More update from my side:

(1) MinGW-w64:

I think we should take "mingw-builds", although it uses a different way to
build GCC.

The Rtools with GCC 4.6.3 used the cross-compiling method: it builds a
cross-compiler and then generates the Windows binaries. But I can't get
multilib support by using this method.

So "mingw-builds" seems a better solution, since it has multilib support.

(2) numerical precision

For reference, the bug is from
https://github.com/wch/r-source/blob/trunk/src/main/arithmetic.c#L217

Best wishes,

KK

